## Introduction
OmiSciDB is an open-source platform for data analysis, web crawling, and structured data sharing across multiple domains in Vietnam. It aims to provide a robust ecosystem for researchers, developers, and organizations to collect, process, and distribute thematic datasets efficiently.

## Features

âœ… **Data Crawling & Aggregation**: Automates data extraction from various sources, ensuring up-to-date and structured datasets.  
âœ… **Multi-Domain Support**: Covers fields such as demographics, economics, urban planning, and product analytics.  
âœ… **Open-Source & Community-Driven**: Encourages contributions from researchers, developers, and data enthusiasts.  
âœ… **Scalability & Performance**: Optimized for handling large-scale datasets efficiently.  
âœ… **API & Query Engine**: Provides REST and GraphQL APIs for seamless data access and integration.  
âœ… **Secure & Controlled Access**: Implements authentication, role-based access, and data privacy mechanisms.  
âœ… **Real-Time Data Processing**: Supports live data streams and analytics pipelines.  

## Use Cases

| Sector                  | Applications |
|-------------------------|-------------|
| **Government & Public Sector** | Crawling and analyzing demographic and economic data for policy-making. |
| **Business Intelligence** | Aggregating and analyzing market trends, consumer behavior, and product analytics. |
| **Academic Research** | Supporting researchers with structured datasets for analysis and model training. |
| **Media & Journalism** | Enabling fact-based reporting through access to verified datasets. |

## Tech Stack

| Component   | Technology |
|------------|-----------|
| **Backend** | Node.js, Express.js, Prisma, MongoDB/PostgreSQL |
| **Frontend** | React, Next.js, Tailwind CSS |
| **Data Crawling** | Puppeteer, Scrapy, BeautifulSoup |
| **Authentication** | OAuth, JWT-based authentication |
| **Real-Time Processing** | WebSockets, Kafka, Apache Spark |
| **CI/CD** | GitHub Actions, Docker, Kubernetes |

## Installation & Setup

```sh
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/OmiSciDB.git
cd OmiSciDB

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Configure environment variables
cp .env.example .env
# Update the `.env` file with the necessary database and API configurations.

# Start the development server
npm run dev
```

